<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,153,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">
Abdomen parallel-sided, slender in both sexes; eighth sternite and tergite well developed and fully visible in male; pygophore about one eighth length of abdomen, laterally slightly compressed, without any process, moderately sclerotized dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[445,526,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1742,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–15. Ploiaria mellea McAtee &amp; Malloch, 1926. Structural details. 7, anterior half of body in lateral view; 8, foreleg details in lateral view, inset first basal seta; 9, forewing; 10–12, pygophore in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views, respectively; 13, lateral view of phallus; 14, spine-like processes of endosoma; 15, parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3754820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3754820/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) and well sclerotized laterally (
<figureCitation box="[876,959,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1742,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–15. Ploiaria mellea McAtee &amp; Malloch, 1926. Structural details. 7, anterior half of body in lateral view; 8, foreleg details in lateral view, inset first basal seta; 9, forewing; 10–12, pygophore in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views, respectively; 13, lateral view of phallus; 14, spine-like processes of endosoma; 15, parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3754820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3754820/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); parameres bent and overlapping at tip, as seen in situ from ventral side (
<figureCitation box="[490,571,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1742,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–15. Ploiaria mellea McAtee &amp; Malloch, 1926. Structural details. 7, anterior half of body in lateral view; 8, foreleg details in lateral view, inset first basal seta; 9, forewing; 10–12, pygophore in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views, respectively; 13, lateral view of phallus; 14, spine-like processes of endosoma; 15, parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3754820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3754820/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); phallus long, symmetrical, extending backward into eighth segment as seen in ventral and lateral view of pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[613,747,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1742,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–15. Ploiaria mellea McAtee &amp; Malloch, 1926. Structural details. 7, anterior half of body in lateral view; 8, foreleg details in lateral view, inset first basal seta; 9, forewing; 10–12, pygophore in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views, respectively; 13, lateral view of phallus; 14, spine-like processes of endosoma; 15, parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3754820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3754820/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
); articulatory apparatus well developed, occupying more than half length of phallus; phallotheca membranous, endosoma with two rows of elongate processes that are broad at base and narrowed apically (
<figureCitation box="[472,608,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1742,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–15. Ploiaria mellea McAtee &amp; Malloch, 1926. Structural details. 7, anterior half of body in lateral view; 8, foreleg details in lateral view, inset first basal seta; 9, forewing; 10–12, pygophore in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views, respectively; 13, lateral view of phallus; 14, spine-like processes of endosoma; 15, parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3754820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3754820/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Figs. 13, 14</figureCitation>
). Parameres small, curved, swollen before middle, setose distally, its apex sharp (
<figureCitation box="[227,311,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1742,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,453,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–15. Ploiaria mellea McAtee &amp; Malloch, 1926. Structural details. 7, anterior half of body in lateral view; 8, foreleg details in lateral view, inset first basal seta; 9, forewing; 10–12, pygophore in dorsal, ventral, and lateral views, respectively; 13, lateral view of phallus; 14, spine-like processes of endosoma; 15, parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3754820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3754820/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
